title: Yellowjackets Win UMAC in Return Season
text:
Yellowjackets Win UMAC in Return Season 
By Norman Seawright III Yellowjackets Win UMAC in Return Season October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 8:15 PM CDT 
Alexandria, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- In its first year of reinstatement since the 2008-2009 season, the University of Wisconsin-Superior women's golf team won its first-ever Upper Midwest Athletic Conference (UMAC) Championship. 
The team kept its lead in two days of competition, scoring 1170 as a team to win. Hayley Botten shot an 88 on the second day, leading her to finish third individually, while Allie Nelson's 100 put her in eighth place.
